# Local `go build` output. The cross-verify workflow uses `go run` and never
# builds a binary; these executables only appear when someone runs
# `go build ./...` locally to check a module compiles. Never commit them —
# they are 2.7 MB platform-specific artifacts (a committed binary in a crypto
# verification repo is a supply-chain smell).
/mldsa87-go/mldsa87-go
/dilithium5-go/dilithium5-go
